attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, EABI4 version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a Mozi botnet variant targeting ARM-based Linux systems, specifically IoT devices/routers. It exhibits multiple malicious behaviors: 1) Network Exploitation: It uses SSDP and UPnP (sub_26e8c, sub_27834) to perform NAT traversal via AddPortMapping and scans for vulnerable HNAP and SOAP interfaces. 2) Host Hardening: It aggressively modifies iptables rules to drop traffic on management ports (22, 23, 2323, 7547) and kills common services like telnetd and scfgmgr to maintain exclusive control (sub_1631c, sub_200e8). 3) Persistence: It remounts partitions as read-write and installs a persistence script named S95baby.sh (sub_1732c, sub_1697c). 4) Botnet Logic: It uses specific tags ([cnc], [dip], [atk]) to parse configuration data, employs custom obfuscation for strings, and references Mozi-specific artifacts like 'Mozi.m' and 'Mozi.a'.
